SUMMARY—Revises provisions relating to county hospitals and
county hospital districts. (BDR 40-559)
FISCAL NOTE: Effect on Local Government: No.
Effect on the State: No.
~
EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to health care; revising provisions governing the
employment and training of certain physicians by a
county hospital or county hospital district; authorizing a
county or district hospital to contract for the provision of
certain services; authorizing a county or district hospital
to form a separate organization for certain purposes; and
providing other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law authorizes a county or group of counties to establish a public
2 hospital. (NRS 450.020) Existing law also authorizes a board of county
3 commissioners to establish a county hospital district to operate a district hospital or
4 otherwise provide the services of a hospital to the residents of this State. (NRS
5 450.590, 450.610, 450.630, 450.710) Existing law authorizes the governing body of
6 a county hospital or a county hospital district to: (1) employ physicians, interns and
7 dentists, on a full-time or part-time basis, and fix their compensations; and (2)
8 control the admission of such physicians and interns to the staff of the hospital by
9 promulgating appropriate rules, regulations and standards governing those
10 appointments. (NRS 450.180, 450.640) Existing law further authorizes the
11 governing body of a county hospital to institute and maintain training programs in
12 the county hospital for resident physicians, interns and postgraduates that meet
13 certain accreditation standards. (NRS 450.455) Sections 1 and 3 of this bill remove
14 interns from the list of persons that the governing body of a county hospital or
15 county hospital district may employ, and instead, authorizes such a governing body
16 to employ and control the admission of residents and fellows and fix their
17 compensation. Section 2 of this bill makes a conforming change to authorize a
18 county hospital to institute and maintain training programs for fellows in addition
19 to resident physicians. Section 2 also updates the name of an accrediting
20 organization for medical residencies.
